Winner of $15,000 and the Ursula and Gilbert Farfel Prize for Investigative Reporting: Spencer S. Hsu of The Washington Post
Roy W. Howard Award for Public Service, the winner: Chicago Tribune for "Playing with Fire"
Digital Innovation winner: The New York Times
TV/Cable for international/national coverage winner: PBS newsmagazine Need to Know and The Investigative Fund at The Nation Institute
TV/Cable for local coverage: the winner is KMGH-TV, Denver
Radio winner is WBEZ, Chicago Public Media
Community Journalism winner is Brandon Stahl of the Duluth News Tribune in Minnesota
Winner of the William Brewster Styles Award for Business/Economics Reporting is Pittsburgh Tribune-Review
Photojournalism winner is Lisa Krantz of the San Antonio Express-News
Edward Willis Scripps Award for Distinguished Service to the First Amendment is The Wall Street Journal for "Watched."
Meeman Award for environmental reporting are Kenneth R. Weiss and Rick Loomis of the Los Angeles Times.
Breaking News winner is The Denver Post.
Human interest winner is Michael M. Phillips of The Wall Street Journal.
Commentary winner is James Carroll of The Boston Globe
Editorial writing: winner is Tim Nickens of the Tampa Bay Times
